Program: Outlook
Title: Diversity of Life and Culture in Trinidad and Tobago
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbrfb
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
A look at life in Trinidad and Tobago including the religious group The Brothers Providence using traditional methods to make molasses. Also, the risks of being a miner in Ukraine. Finally, the stories of the silkies (seals) in Celtic literature.